@@ -140,4 +140,10 @@
 - **Add item hit & shield pop audio**: Added `playItemHit()` (descending square wave + noise burst) for when the player is struck by an item, and `playShieldPop()` (rising sine + high-pass noise burst) for when a shield blocks a hit or expires. Both are triggered via `_itemHitFrame`/`_shieldPopFrame` flags on the kart, consumed each frame in `main.js`. Shield expiry now also plays the pop sound and emits blue particles (previously it just silently disappeared).
 - **Star golden trail particles**: Added `emitStarTrail()` to particles.js that spawns gold/yellow particles scattering from the kart's sides and rear. Triggered at 25Hz while `starActive` is true. Added `starT` accumulator to the visual update loop, properly reset on race start and quit.
 - **Homing pigeon upward bounce**: Per spec ("target bounces upward slightly 1.5 voxels"), `applyItemHit` for `homingPigeon` now sets `verticalVelocity = 8` and `onGround = false` on the hit kart, causing a visible upward pop before gravity brings it back down.
-- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). Star timer confirmed at 3s (decays to ~1.08 after 2s), invincibleTimer confirmed 0. Shield timer confirmed at 4s. Player picks up items normally. All 8 karts racing on every track.
\ No newline at end of file
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). Star timer confirmed at 3s (decays to ~1.08 after 2s), invincibleTimer confirmed 0. Shield timer confirmed at 4s. Player picks up items normally. All 8 karts racing on every track.
+
+## Iteration 22 — Focus: Track Integrity
+- **Snap last road sample to first for watertight closure**: On a closed CatmullRom curve, `getPointAt(0)` and `getPointAt(1)` should be identical, but floating-point drift in tangent/perpendicular computation caused the last sample's left/right edge positions to differ from the first sample's by up to 4.17 units (Mossy Canyon) and 2.22 units (Neon Grid). This left physical gaps in the wall barrier at the start/finish line through which karts could escape. Now the last sample's pos, leftEdge, rightEdge, tangent, perp, width, and bankAngle are all snapped to exactly match the first sample. Post-fix: all closure gaps measure 0.0000 on every track.
+- **T-based sector assignment for wall collision lookup**: Previously, wall sectors were built by dividing wall indices evenly (`wallsPerSector = ceil(totalWalls/numSectors)`). Since `addWallSegment` skips very short segments (`len < 0.1`), the sequential index-based division could misalign sectors vs the spline t-value lookup (`sectorIdx = floor(nearest.t * numSectors)`) used by the physics system. Now each wall stores its source sample's spline `t` value (`wall.sampleT`), and `buildSectors` assigns walls to sectors via `floor(sampleT * numSectors)`. This guarantees that the physics sector lookup always finds the correct walls regardless of wall-skip patterns. Sector sizes are now near-perfectly balanced (±3 walls max across 20 sectors on all tracks).
+- **Start/finish line checkered visual marker**: Added `buildStartFinishLine()` that creates an alternating black/white 8-square checkered stripe across the road at t=0. The marker is 2 units deep along the track tangent and rendered slightly above the road surface (`y + 0.05`) with `renderOrder=1` to prevent z-fighting. Uses vertex colors (`MeshBasicMaterial` with `vertexColors`) for zero texture overhead. Provides a clear visual landmark for the lap line on all 4 tracks.
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors across all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). All closure gaps 0.0000 (pos, leftEdge, rightEdge). All 1241–1780 walls per track have valid sampleT values. No empty sectors. All 8 karts alive and on ground during active gameplay on every track. Sector balance confirmed: Sunset Bay ±3, Mossy Canyon ±3, Neon Grid ±3, Volcano Peak ±2.
\ No newline at end of file
